<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="breadcrumb"><a href="/modules">← Back to modules</a></p>

    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Reporting and export capability</p>
      <h1>Reports & Export Capability</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        This page shows how operational data can be summarised and exported so it remains useful
        outside the system itself.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="stat-grid">
      <article class="stat">
        <strong><%= stats.recordsTotal %></strong>
        <span>Total records</span>
      </article>
      <article class="stat">
        <strong><%= stats.recordsActive %></strong>
        <span>Active records</span>
      </article>
      <article class="stat">
        <strong><%= stats.invoicesTotal %></strong>
        <span>Total invoices</span>
      </article>
      <article class="stat">
        <strong><%= stats.invoicesOpen %></strong>
        <span>Open invoices</span>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid module-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Invoice export</h3>
        <p>
          Export invoice data as CSV for finance, reconciliation or wider reporting workflows.
        </p>
        <a class="btn" href="/modules/invoices-export.csv">Export invoice CSV</a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Records visibility</h3>
        <p>
          Records stay reviewable and structured, helping preserve operational history over time.
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/modules/records">View records</a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Workflow context</h3>
        <p>
          Reporting becomes more useful when bookings, records and invoices are treated as connected work rather than isolated screens.
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/workflow">View workflow overview</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
